<teaserTitle>Avocado Shrimp</teaserTitle>
<teaserText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p>Avocado with Shrimp is a Mediterrenean favorite that is very quick to prepare, yet delicious.</p></div></teaserText>
<detailText grammarName="coremedia-richtext-1.0"><div xmlns="http://www.coremedia.com/2003/richtext-1.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"><p class="p--heading-2">Introduction</p><p>On a hot summer day, you need refereshing starters: Avocado with Shrimp is a Mediterrenean favorite that is very quick to prepare, yet delicious. Cut a ripe avocado into halves and drizzle with lemon juice and add salt and pepper. Then add some shrimp. You may want to try topping off the avocado with a "Sauce Americaine" - just mix sour cream with Ketchup and add salt to taste.</p><p> </p><p class="p--heading-2">Ingredients</p><ul><li>3 medium avocados, halved, pit and skin removed</li><li>4 oz crab meat</li><li>5 large shrimp, boiled, chilled and then chopped into small chunks</li><li>1 tablespoon red bell pepper, small dice</li><li>1 tablespoon red onion, small dice</li><li>1 tablespoon celery, small dice</li><li>½ tablespoon parsley, small dice</li><li>1 ½ tablespoon lite mayo</li><li>Fresh black pepper</li><li>Chili lime sauce</li><li>¼ cup lite mayo</li><li>1 tablespoon siracha sauce</li><li>2 tablespoon Chili Lime Cholula</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Preparation</p><ul><li>Combine all ingredients together and mix well</li><li>Scoop the crab &amp; shrimp mixture onto the avocado</li><li>Squirt the sauce over the avocado and sprinkle with parsley</li></ul><p class="p--heading-2">Serving Suggestion</p><p>For something a bit more dressed up but still deliciously easy to prepare, look to shrimp scampi, a quick-fix classic that pairs garlic, lemon and often a splash of white wine with the tender shellfish.</p></div></detailText>
